      • getConstrainedType

        public List<JAXBElement<? extends ConstrainedType>> getConstrainedType()
        R708 DomainType Gets the value of the constrainedType property.

        This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the constrainedType property.

        For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 

            getConstrainedType().add(newItem);

        Objects of the following type(s) are allowed in the list JAXBElement<EnumeratedType> JAXBElement<RealType> JAXBElement<IntegerType> JAXBElement<RationalType> JAXBElement<SymbolicType> JAXBElement<ConstrainedType> JAXBElement<AtomicType> JAXBElement<BooleanType> JAXBElement<StructuredType>
